This paper discusses a peer-to-peer system for preserving access to journals and archival information published on the web. The system involves a large number of independent web caches that cooperate to detect and repair damage to their content by voting in "opinion polls." The paper also presents a novel protocol for voting in systems of this kind, which incorporates rate limitation and intrusion detection. Based on this description, the most likely sub-category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), followed by cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), and cs.SE (Software Engineering).
